# SSH Brute Force Detection Lab

## Objective
Simulate failed SSH login attempts and analyze Linux authentication logs.

## Environment
- Kali Linux
- Ubuntu Server
- VirtualBox

## Tools Used
- journalctl
- grep
- ssh
- systemctl

## Scenario
A Kali Linux machine attempted multiple failed SSH logins against an Ubuntu Server VM.

## Detection
The failed login attempts were detected inside authentication logs.

## Commands Used

```bash
sudo journalctl -u ssh

grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log

